pageContext.claim: “It's not a long time when you consider it's probably the biggest deal ever made.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump is not negotiating a new free trade agreement with China, just trying to smooth over trade differences. Even so, if Trump makes a deal with China, it would not be the biggest trade deal ever made. The Trans Pacific Partnership negotiated by Barack Obama -- which Trump abandoned -- involved trade worth more than $1.5 trillion, double the size of two-way trade between the United States and China.
